Specifications of the Deveel Omni-Channel Messaging API v1

Authentication

oauth2

Security Scheme Type OAuth2
clientCredentials OAuth Flow
Token URL: https://deveel.eu.auth0.com/oauth/token
Scopes:
  • read:channel -

    Read-only access to user Channels

  • create:channel -

    Create new user Channels

  • update:channel -

    Update settings of existing user Channels

  • delete:channel -

    Delete existing user Channels

  • request:terminal -

    Request the assignment of existing or new terminals

  • delete:terminal -

    Delete existing terminals

  • read:terminal -

    Read access to the terminals

  • create:route -

    Create new inbound message routes

  • read:route -

    Read access to message routes

  • update:route -

    Update existing message routes

  • delete:route -

    Delete existing message routes

  • send:message -

    Configure notifications of message state changes

authorizationCode OAuth Flow
Authorization URL: https://deveel.eu.auth0.com/authorize
Token URL: https://deveel.eu.auth0.com/oauth/token
Scopes:
  • read:channel -

    Read-only access to user Channels

  • create:channel -

    Create new user Channels

  • update:channel -

    Update settings of existing user Channels

  • delete:channel -

    Delete existing user Channels

  • request:terminal -

    Request the assignment of existing or new terminals

  • delete:terminal -

    Delete existing terminals

  • read:terminal -

    Read access to the terminals

  • create:route -

    Create new inbound message routes

  • read:route -

    Read access to message routes

  • update:route -

    Update existing message routes

  • delete:route -

    Delete existing message routes

  • send:message -

    Configure notifications of message state changes

Requests the Assignment of a Channel

Authorizations:
oauth2 (request:channel)
Request Body schema:
application/json-patch+json
application/json-patch+json
application/json
text/json
application/*+json
name
required
string^[a-zA-Z0-9_.-]+$

The name of the channel instance

directions
string (ChannelDirections)
Enum: "default" "out" "in" "both"
contentTypes
Array of strings (MessageContentType) Nullable
Items Enum: "text" "html" "multipart" "template"

The types of content allowed by the channel (if not set the channel will be assigned all the allowed content types from the source channel)

senderTypes
Array of strings Nullable

The types of terminals allowed to send messages outbound (if not set the channel will inherit all the allowed types from the source channel)

receiverTypes
Array of strings Nullable

The types of terminals allowed to receive messages inbound (if not set the channel will inherit all the allowed types from the source channel)

object Nullable

The settings specific for the channel instance, integrating or overriding the settings from the source channel

Array of objects (NewChannelTerminal) Nullable

The list of terminals to be bound to the channel

sourceId
required
string

The identifier of the source channel from the inventory

Array of objects (ChannelQuota) Nullable

The usage quotas assigned to the channel

Responses

https://api.ocm.deveel.net/channel/request

Creates a new Channel

Authorizations:
oauth2 (create:channel)
Request Body schema:
application/json-patch+json
application/json-patch+json
application/json
text/json
application/*+json
Array of objects (ChannelQuota) Nullable

The usage quotas to be enforced within the channel

name
required
string^[a-zA-Z0-9_.-]+$

The name of the channel instance

type
required
string (ChannelType)
Enum: "sms" "messenger" "whatsapp" "email" "viber" "rcs" "push" "sandbox"
provider
required
string (ChannelProvider)
Enum: "other" "twilio" "sendgrid" "sendinblue" "facebook" "deveel" "linkmobility" "mailjet"
directions
required
string (ChannelDirections)
Enum: "default" "out" "in" "both"
contentTypes
Array of strings (MessageContentType) Nullable
Items Enum: "text" "html" "multipart" "template"

The list of allowed types of message content

senderTypes
required
Array of strings non-empty

The types of terminals allowed by the channel to send messages outbound

receiverTypes
Array of strings Nullable

The types of terminals allowed by the channel to receive messages inbound

Array of objects (SecureChannelCredentials) Nullable

The credentials that will be used to access the provider of messaging services

object Nullable

Channel-specific settings (supported by the provider)

Array of objects (ChannelTerminal) Nullable

A list of terminals to be bound to the channel

Responses
